
[1]exterior

   EXTE'RIOR, a. [L. from exterus, foreign.]

   1. External; outward; applied to the outside or outer surface of a
   body, and opposed to interior. We speak of the exterior and interior
   surfaces of a concavo-convex lens.

   2. External; on the outside, with reference to a person; extrinsic. We
   speak of an object exterior to a man, as opposed to that which is
   within or in his mind.

         EXTE'RIOR, n. The outward surface; that which is external.

   1. Outward or visible deportment; appearance.
